Finally, the breakthrough comes for Zimbabwe!

commentary: Sikandar Raza to Asghar Afghan, OUT great work from the keeper! The batsman aimed a flick-sweep just wide of the fielder at short fine, but the fielder was around in a flash to stop it. It still looked like the single was on, but he rifled a through to the keeper, who caught it cleanly and then turned in a flash to break the stumps right between his own legs - he was in front of them when he caught the ball.

commentary: Sikandar Raza to Najibullah Zadran, OUT stumped! Najibullah ran down the track, looking to smite the ball all the way onto 1st Avenue, which runs along the southern side of the ground ... But he ran right past the ball, which spun sharply past him, and Mutumbami had plenty of time to softly displace a single bail from the stumps. Afghanistan lose another, and Zimbabwe are clawing their way back into the game.

commentary: Rashid Khan to Williams, 1 run quick run, and another collision between batsman and fielder! It meant that Williams couldn't get into the crease, but fortunately the throw went wide, as the batsmen had chanced a quick single. That would have been a controversial dismissal, with Rashid getting around and directly into the batsman's path. I don't think it was deliberate.

commentary: Rashid Khan to Williams, OUT game over, Afghanistan win! Williams comes down the track, swings past the ball, and Shahzad breaks the stumps. Shahzad immediately starts pulling stumps out of the ground, tossing one each to the fielders on either side of him and keeping one as a memento for himself. Williams looks shell shocked as he walks off. The crowd stand to applaud him, and he gives them a wave, but there's no smile on his face.

Williams looks shell shocked as he walks off. The crowd stand to applaud him, and he gives them a wave, but there's no smile on his face.
